&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Orthopaedic Team Manager/&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Senior Sister/Theatre Practitioner &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Main Theatres is looking for a dynamic, dedicated, and hardworking experienced trained nurse or ODP to lead in Orthopaedics.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be expected to provide high-quality patient care, support and supervise theatre staff and take charge of the clinical area in the absence of the Matron.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for someone with an extensive Orthopaedic Theatre experience and a Mentorship qualification to come and join our unit. This role will give you the opportunity to develop both your clinical and managerial knowledge and skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will also to be able to professionally develop by undertaking the many in house training and external courses offered.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We carry out a wide variety of Surgery including Trauma Orthopaedics, CEPOD, General, and Urology, Plastics, ENT and Maxillofacial, Gynaecology and Laparoscopic procedures.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For more information or to arrange an informal visit, please contact Barbara Raine on&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;020 8946 7711 Ext 3393 / 3039 or Barbara.Raine1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews are likely to take place W/C 30th November&lt;/p&gt;
